                            <comment id="12635877" author="mikedd" created="Tue, 30 Sep 2008 23:24:37 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in revision 700603. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The change adds a dbcp.args property to pom.xml. The property is passed in to the surefire test harness and used when to configure the connection pool.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The property may be set on the command line  or in a profile in .m2/settings.xml. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example command line usage : &lt;br/&gt;
$ mvn test -Ddbcp.args=MaxActive =5,MaxIdle=2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example settings.xml usage: &lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;profile&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;id&amp;gt;unreasonably-large-pool&amp;lt;id&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;properties&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
         &amp;lt;dbcp.args&amp;gt;MaxActive=1000,MaxIdle=0,MaxWait=500&amp;lt;/dbcp.args&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/properties&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/profile&amp;gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$ mvn test -Punreasonably-large-pool&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;More practical examples include increasing the MaxIdle to avoid the overhead of creating connections. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The default settings may be found in pom.xml (openjpa-persistence-jdbc) and are currently MaxActive=100,MaxIdle=0,MaxWait=10000&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12636087" author="milosz" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2008 17:36:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for addressing this. I have tested this in my environment and works fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was thinking of updating the Unit Tests page on wiki but it seems this requires some privileges.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12636138" author="mikedd" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2008 20:43:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Good point. Currently most of the permissions on the wiki are restricted to OpenJPA developers and admins. If I&apos;m reading the permissions correctly members of the asf-cla group in confluence can also add pages. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we&apos;d be better served to go with something similar to Geronimo&apos;s approach (seen here : &lt;a href=&quot;http://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/geronimo/Geronimo+cwiki+documentation+architecture&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/geronimo/Geronimo+cwiki+documentation+architecture&lt;/a&gt; ) with a separate group of contributors who can add to the wiki. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll propose this on the developer mailing list, but I suspect it&apos;s policy to require a CLA before anyone can add to an Apache website (since the wiki is our website it may require a CLA as well). &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
